  "text": "Requiring that the initial and final states of a trajectory be the same is analogous to one of the requirements that must be satisfied for a simulation to reach a regeneration point [CITATION_1] . In both cases, this objective eliminates \"end effects\" that complicate the analysis by creating imbalances. However, equality of the initial and final states is a substantially weaker condition since any state can serve as the initial and final state of the trajectory.",
